About 40 min after my shot I started feeling tightness (like asthma) in my chest. I ended up needing 6 puffs from my inhaler. (I had also experienced feeling very agitated throughout that day and night). The periodic daily need for the i hailer continued and so I called Moderna and the woman I spoke with told me that the breathing issue was a reaction (she was not as sure about the feeling of agitation) and that when I got my second dose to have them observe for an hour. Over the weeks since that first breathing episode it has continued daily and required the use of my in hailer. In the last few days it has been worse than before and I?ve had a mild headache for about 3 days.  Tomorrow is my shot. I didn?t realize about reporting here until I read about it today.  Since I have a n old history of asthma (though it?s been a relative ?non issue? for years (except  when I get a cold in my chest), but I would want this known for other people with asthma, because it?s definitely going on and strange. (Nothing preventing me from my normal day - but for sure my days have not been ?normal?.  I plan on seeing my doctor to get new medicine for the nebulizer and  likely stronger type asthma medication until it goes away)
HISTORY: History of asthma, but no trouble with it really since I had pertussis in 2014. (Generally only if I catch something that goes into my chest like cold or flu) A couple years back almost -  when I swam indoors a lot - it could get aggravated by chlorine fumes.    Other than that I have had no issues  until literally 40 min after my first shot.  I DID call Moderna and report it and they told me it was a reaction, so I was thinking it would pass, but it hasn?t. They told me to be observed for an hour when I get my shot tomorrow.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Progress NotesFamily Medicine Cosigned/8/2021 10:39 AM  COVID VACCINE CLINIC     a 56 y.o. female who was seen at COVID Vaccine Clinic today for her first  dose of the COVID 19 vaccination.    She was given the Pfizer vaccination in the right deltoid muscle.   During her 15 minute waiting period after the injection, the patient began to experience tingling/shaking, short of breath.  She denied rash, hives, welts, difficulty swallowing, wheezing, throat tightness, hoarseness, stridor, itching, lightheadedness, dizziness, facial swelling, lip swelling and tongue swelling.   This provider was notified of patient reaction and she was then assessed in the emergency bay area.   Monitored patient for severe reaction symptoms, including but not limited to blood pressure abnormality , rapid progression of symptoms and respiratory distress.   PMH: depression, takes Abilify and Cymbalta. GERD on Protonix. Lipitor for cholesterol.     ALLERGY REVIEW OF SYSTEMS:  Patient complains of chills ("shaky") and shortness of breath   Patient denies fever, malaise/fatigue, facial swelling, sore throat, frequent throat clearing, eyes watering, eyes itching, puffy eyes, eye redness, cough, chest tightness, wheezing, rash, hives, eczema, itching of skin, abdominal pain, muscle aches, joint pain, dizziness and headaches    tingling in hands.:     Previous Reactions: none    Objective    Vitals Vitals:   03/08/21 0833 03/08/21 0851 BP: 133/78 123/71 BP Location: Left arm   Patient Position: Sitting   Pulse: 95 81 SpO2: 99% 98%      Blood Sugar 117 collected at 0839     Physical Exam Constitutional:      General: She is not in acute distress.    Appearance: Normal appearance. She is well-developed. She is not diaphoretic.  HENT:     Mouth/Throat:     Mouth: Mucous membranes are moist.     Pharynx: Oropharynx is clear.  Eyes:     Extraocular Movements: Extraocular movements intact.     Conjunctiva/sclera: Conjunctivae normal.     Pupils: Pupils are equal, round, and reactive to light.  Cardiovascular:     Rate and Rhythm: Normal rate and regular rhythm.     Pulses: Normal pulses.     Heart sounds: Normal heart sounds.  Pulmonary:     Effort: Pulmonary effort is normal. No respiratory distress.     Breath sounds: Normal breath sounds. No wheezing.     Comments: intially hyperventilating but improved after removal of mask. Eupnea at discharge.  Skin:    General: Skin is warm and dry.  Neurological:     General: No focal deficit present.     Mental Status: She is alert and oriented to person, place, and time.     Gait: Gait normal.  Psychiatric:        Mood and Affect: Mood is anxious.        Behavior: Behavior normal.        Thought Content: Thought content normal.        Judgment: Judgment normal.     Comments: Hyperventilating upon arrival to bay. Mask taken off to assist with this along with instructions on deep breathing.          Assessment/Plan  Treatment included: water, snacks and pepcid Follow up response to treatment: excellent. Patient discharge: Stable to go home and follow up with PCP.  Differential Diagnosis: Vaccine-Related Anxiety (include misc mental health)   Pt observed in the bay for approx. 15 minutes. Pt greatly improved with treatments above.  Pt encouraged to eat 30 minutes prior to next vaccine.  She reports that she is appreciative of her care today. F/up with pcp as needed.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 6 hours after vaccination I experienced soreness at the site of the injection (scale of 4-5).  Overnight the pain got worse (scale 6 or more).  The pain at the site was more than I have experienced with a tetanus shot.  It was uncomfortable to sleep or rollover.  The pain was more than I have had with any previous injection.  The next morning which is today, I examined the site of the injection and saw that the injection site was at the top of the deltoid muscle approaching the bursar.  I am not a large individual at 5' 8" and 140 pounds.  My deltoid is not very large and the injection was above the thickest part of the deltoid.  I am a pharmacist and give injections, I also had my wife look at it, she is also a injection administering pharmacist.  We both determined the injection site was outside the normal injection location of the deltoid.  It is now over 24 hours since the injection, and the pain/discomfort is subsiding.  At this point the pain is similar to a tetanus shot and acceptable (scale 2-3).

I received the vaccine on Friday, February 26th, 2021, around 10:20am.  I was fine throughout the day. I was also fine all day on Saturday, February 27th, 2021. Sunday, February 28th, 2021 at 1:30am, I woke up from sleep with double vision, dizziness, and lightheadedness. I went to use my bathroom, and began to feel week. I was still very lightheaded, and weak. I felt as though I was going to faint. My ears started to feel really warm, and I then vomited. I started feeling lightheaded and weak once again, and then suddenly had diarrhea. I was so dizzy, but managed to head to my bed to sleep. Every single day since, I have been dizzy and losing my balance. I wake up, walk around, and sleep dizzy. Then on Friday, March 5th, 2021 I developed a large lump directly under my armpit. I could not take the dizziness any longer and I went to the ER on Monday, March 8th. I was then diagnosed with vertigo and told that I most likely had lymphodenopathy.  Till this day, I am still having dizziness and will be seeing an ENT doctor. I also still have the lump under my armpit. My next dose is, March 19th, 2021.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 18 year old female came to hospital for chest tightness, choking sensation in the throat as well as skin rash after receiving COVID-19 vaccine.  Initially patient presented to emergency room but subsequently discharged on steroid and Benadryl.  Patient had continued episode of choking as well as chest tightness and skin rash for that patient came back to emergency room.  Patient had received total 5 doses of epi pen because of that.  Patient was admitted to medical floor initially.  Patient was given steroid, Benadryl and famotidine.  Patient had 2 episodes on medical floor where she started feeling choking and chest tightness.  Patient remained stable hemodynamically except for tachycardia.  Patient was transferred to intensive care unit for close monitoring.  D-dimer was negative, urine tox screen was negative, COVID-19 PCR was negative, EKG showed sinus tachycardia.  CT scan of neck was negative.  We had discussed that patient has remained stable hemodynamically in the intensive care unit and discharge planning was discussed and patient was getting ready to be discharged when she had another episode where after drinking soda patient started having that choking sensation, patient remained stable hemodynamically during this episode as well.  Her symptoms had improved.  She looked visibly anxious.  Patient was monitored in the ICU for few more hours and patient remained stable.  I checked back on her and she was able to eat her lunch.  She probably had a allergic reaction to more than a vaccine but subsequent episodes are thought to be secondary to anxiety attack given situation.

Extreme soreness (couldn't move my arm fully), as well as fatigue and muscle pain, nausea, and headaches.  I couldn't move half of the day and was in so much pain I could not leave my room.  My joints felt like they were burning and I couldn't stay in one position too long (more than 15-30 minutes) or I would get back pain.  I couldn't sleep due to the pain

the day after the vaccine I slept all day.  Next day felt 100% better.  On the 3rd day I began feeling exhaustion and weakness as though I had been very sick and my body was having difficulty recovering.  20 years ago I had an autoimmune issue (Chronic Fatigue Syndrome) and asthma that took me about 10 years to get under control. I started getting shortness of breathe and I was concerned I may have gotten COVID, but I since took a test and do not and have never tested positive (about 5 tests).  I had 2 days of Renaud's incidence when one segment of my right forefinger completely drained of blood, and turned white.  (Same finger both days). It took me 10 minutes of massage and windmills with my arm to bring color back to the finger.  The shortness of breathe continues weeks later and it appears my asthma has returned.  Went to the doctor last week and we are starting with and inhaler to see if that takes care of it.  I have had to use it every day since I got prescription 3/6 - all day the first day, lesser since.  Still shortness of breathe and feeling compromised.    My sister has worse autoimmune problems and MSRA.  After her Moderna vaccine last week she was confined to bed the whole week with her 1st vaccination.  She had not been exposed to COVID that she is aware of. Neither of us ever smoked.  Could be our lungs were already compromised with both parents heavy smokers and growing up where all the smog from the 1960's would linger. Our breathing would ache from exertion.  A brother, once a heavy smoker, has had emphysema, and serious heart damage from a heart attack, and suffers from a lack of O2.  He has not had a shot yet and we are concerned about his response.
LAB_DATA: Just COVID19 screening with negative results at this point. If no improvement we plan an xray and if difficulty breathing increases I have been instructed to go to emergency.  Drs visit was online, not in person.

central epithelial defect; neurotrophic keratopathy; Information has been received from a lawyer referring to a male patient of unknown age regarding a case in litigation. Information about concurrent condition, history condition and concomitant medication was not reported. On or around 11-OCT-2013, the patient was vaccinated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) (strength, dose, route, lot# and expiration date unknown) for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster). Shortly after receiving zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient suffered severely painful impaired vision, redness in left eye and decreased visual acuity. The patient was diagnosed with neurotrophic keratopathy and central epithelial defect. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient's symptoms have resulted in physical limitations not present prior to using the vaccine. The patient also experiences mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of his condition. As a result of the manufacture, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient has suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. The outcome of the events neurotrophic keratopathy and central epithelial defect was considered to be not recovered and causal relationship was assessed as related.    The lawyer considered the events neurotrophic keratopathy and central epithelial defect to be disability.   Upon internal review, central epithelial defect was determined to be medically significant.

Guillain-Barre syndrome; tingling extended over his entire body; lightheaded; malaise; flu syndrome; This case was reported by a lawyer and described the occurrence of guillain barre syndrome in a 66-year-old male patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) (batch number unk, expiry date unknown) for prophylaxis.   On 7th January 2019, the patient received Shingrix (intramuscular). On 8th January 2019, 1 days after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced malaise and flu syndrome. On 11th January 2019, the patient experienced light headedness. On 14th January 2019, the patient experienced tingling. On an unknown date, the patient experienced guillain barre syndrome (serious criteria GSK medically significant). The action taken with Shingrix was unknown. On an unknown date, the outcome of the guillain barre syndrome, malaise, flu syndrome, light headedness and tingling were unknown.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the guillain barre syndrome, malaise, flu syndrome, light headedness and tingling to be related to Shingrix.  additional details: The initial information was received on 24 February 2021 via medical record (case is medically confirmed). The patient ingested shingrix vaccine on 07 January 2019. January 7, he had the SHINGRIX vaccine. January 8, he had malaise and a flu syndrome. January 11, he felt lightheaded and faint with tingling beginning in his toes, extending up his leg to knees. January 14, the tingling extended over his entire body. His body was red, He felt lethargic. He had no actual muscle weakness but noted decreased functional ability at the gym. The diagnosis of Guillain-Barre was made. He received IVIG in the hospital. The tingling decreased and has receded such that it is present from the knee down through his shins into his feet. He notes the occasional tingling in his hands since the onset of symptoms. His walking and balance are 80% improved. His balance and coordination are improved, and he is not dropping objects.

And I did some CBD during the day sometimes.   Still did the gaba and CBD at night.   Sometimes the pain was so bad it burned. From old injuries, my muscles are weaker because I've rested too much.   My need to sleep was extreme and I was taking long naps during the day and sleeping at night. I also want to report something many of my friends are reporting... and that is a sense of euphoria after the shot.  I also had that.  BUT I know that that can be caused by a kick into effect of hormones.   And I think one or more of the ingredients are apt to cause that (like the hydrocarbons/plastics).  they can serve as synthetic hormones.   People are thinking that the euphoria was psychological because of relief.   I know better and I want this explained to people.   It is not ok to let them believe this.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Employee received the first dose of the COVID 19 vaccine on 1/22/2021 in her left deltoid. At the time she received the first dose she only had a sore left arm. Two days after receiving the vaccine she experienced shooting, sharp pain when she tried to lift her left arm forward or to the side. Pain was 8 out of 10. She saw her primary care doctor, on 2/1/21. He advised her to wait to see if the symptoms got better. She continued to have decreased range of motion and shooting, sharp pain when she moved her left arm. She saw an orthopedic doctor on 2/10/2021 who did an x-ray and MRI. The MRI showed calcification of the bursa in her left shoulder. This doctor recommended cortisone injections. Employee received the first dose of the COVID 19 vaccine on 1/22/2021 in her left deltoid. At the time she received the first dose she only had a sore left arm. Two days after receiving the vaccine she experienced shooting, sharp pain when she tried to lift her left arm forward or to the side. Pain was 8 out of 10. She saw her primary care doctor,  on 2/1/21. He advised her to wait to see if the symptoms got better. She continued to have decreased range of motion and shooting, sharp pain when she moved her left arm. She saw an orthopedic doctor on 2/10/2021 who did an x-ray and MRI. The MRI showed calcification of the bursa in her left shoulder. This doctor recommended cortisone injections, but the employee did not want to do that. On 3/10/2021 she saw an orthopedic surgeon who specializes in shoulders. Drtold the employee she had a shoulder injury related to vaccine administration (SIRVA) because the needle from the COVID 19 vaccine went into the bursa sac in her left shoulder. He is recommending physical therapy for treatment. Employee reports currently the shooting, sharp pain is gone and now there is a dull ache in her shoulder. The employee states she received the second COVID vaccine, with a smaller needle, with no adverse effects.

Within 1 minute of vaccine being injected. I started to feel dizzy. I was wheeled in wheelchair to observation area. I kept feeling more dizzy and started to feel tingly in my fingers and legs (both sides equally) After 15 minute observation time was over, I tried to stand up and immediately sat down again as a wave of dizziness  hit me. Doctor in observation area saw me and came over. I told him how I felt. He put his fingers to my wrist and felt my pulse. It was initially between 40 and 90, then steadied off around 90-100. He called for EMTs on duty to come over with a stretcher because he thought I should be laid flat. The EMT took my blood pressure and it was 155/94. The doctor said at one point my pulse was thready. By this point the dizziness was stronger and I felt tingly in my teeth as well as other areas. I was asked about my breathing and I said that it was okay. An ambulance was called for and arrived. I don't remember the exact time. The moved me from the wheelchair to a stretcher. I could not stand up on my own and lurched toward the stretcher. I am grateful strong people were there to get me on stretcher and strapped in. All throughout this my normally barely noticeable Atrial Fibrillation was quite apparent and more erratic. This was a major reason for ambulance call. Some of the stroke protocol was done including gripping EMT's fingers equally and following his finger with my eyes. I was very cold throughout. I was brought to the waiting ambulance outside and driven to Medical Center. The EMT took an EKG which showed atrial fibrillation and a line was put into my arm.  When we got to the hospital, I was brought into the triage area and had all my vitals taken. Blood pressure was high, so was pulse then for a half hour, I was very hot and sweated a lot after being cold.

CUR_ILL: I was exposed to Poison Oak on Feb 15.   After my second dose on Covid-19 vaccination on February 22, a "severe" rash spread over my head, neck, belly, sides and upper thighs.  Prescription steroid topicals did nothing.  I saw a dermatologist on Feb 24 who gave me a shot of cortisone.  The rash continued to spread.  After another week he put me on oral steroids 15 mg.  Now I have tapered off to 5 mg per day and the rash is fading slowly.  I have been exposed to poison oak dozens of times in the past without any reaction.  I believe that the severity and persistence of this rash are the result of my having had covid-19 in March 2020 and of this exposure occurring between the two doses of the vaccination.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 9 hours after receiving the vaccine I began developing flu-like symptoms, which quickly escalated. Within a couple of hours I developed a very high fever (which peaked at 104.1 and hovered around 102-103), body-wracking cold chills, extreme lethargy and body aches. The only thing that kept my fever down was 1,000mg of Tylenol every 6 hours, with a cold compress on my head. The symptoms were less severe but still substantial by the following day. On the second night after receiving the vaccine (Monday the 8th) I had nightsweats, but then woke up on the morning of Tuesday the 9th feeling almost completely back to normal. The only other strange thing to happen was waking up today on Thursday the 11th with a giant fever blister on my lip, which I suppose could be attributed to an immune system in temporary disarray or overdrive. I am still very grateful for the vaccine and would do it again, but it was very scary that first night on Sunday the 7th. I don't remember the last time I felt that sick.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: itching

There was no adverse reaction. requested a VAERS report to be filed since the patient was 15.94 years of age and not 16.   Patient was in the presence of parent and has a history of asthma, and Pfizer vaccine was used since it is approved for 16 years of age.

11 minutes after injection, the patient reported her tongue and throat "felt funny". She did not have sob, difficulty breathing, hives, dizziness, light-headedness, or closing up of the airways and thus anaphylaxis was excluded. She was given water and the option to take a dose of benedryl which she did. Symptoms resolved and following up later that day she reported being fine.

Starting 24 hours after second dose, patient experienced fever, chills, body aches, headaches throughout Thursday and Friday.  On Saturday, she noticed a little 'movable lump' on her lower right jaw (opposite side from vaccine site).  By Monday the lump had grown to 3.5cm. SYMPTOM_TEXT: I started having radicular tingling with neck flexion that ran down my left leg starting at the beginning of February. I noted it to a colleague and asked if anyone else who had received the vaccine at the same time as me had any similar effects. I was the only person noted. Slowly the tingling increased and began radiating the entire length of the left leg. It only last for a few seconds at the beginning of flexion then completely resolved. I did not think much of this at the time and figured that it would resolve. On February 27, I began having visual disturbances and symptoms similar to vertigo with a severe nystagmus with a gaze the the right. I attempted a round of azithromycin at this time thinking that there may be an ear infection and that was causing my visual/vertigo like symptoms. There was no improvement with this course of treatment and the visual issues were becoming more of a regular issue. It became hard for me to focus anytime that I would look to my right but was able to focus my eyes while looking forward and the the left. At this time, I opted to have a brain MRI done which was completed on Match 9th as well as having basic labs run. I ended up with an elevated white count on my labs with a left shift. My MRI was read the same day showing a demyelinating process. Multiple neurologist were consulted on this and they believe that my symptoms are not related to MS as the radiologist listed as his top three on his differential but rather what they called post-covid vaccine syndrome, similar to what they are seeing with patients who actually had COVID. I have no medical history, I am not taking any medications and had no symptoms prior to the vaccine. My symptoms were acutely brought on unlike MS and I do not have any of the four most common male characteristics of MS. I do not currently have any muscle weakness, I am not fatigued, it has not progressed to my upper extremities, it does not have a stalking glove approach but rather shoots down, I have no sexual dysfunction. I have been started on a high dose prednisone taper as recommended by the neurologist. My biggest concern is that when I looked for information as a medical provider, I was unable to find anything related to neurological issues and the vaccine. Once, I was placed in contact with multiple neurologist, I was told that they are seen quite a few neurological adverse events.
LAB_DATA: CBC, CMP and MRI or brain completed on 3/9/2021 Follow up CMP, CBC, ESR and CRP are currently pending on 3/11.

On March 3, 2021, a eligible vaccine recipient, patient, received her first dose of Pfizer Covid 19 vaccine at approximately 9:00am.  After a 15 minute observation period, patient was driving home at approximately 9:20am when she began to feel tingling and numbness in her mouth and tightening of the throat.  Patient returned to clinic and informed clinic staff she was having a reaction to the vaccine.  A cardiologist volunteering in the post-immunization observation met with the patient and evaluated her.  The cardiologist was informed by patient that she had a history of allergic reactions to vaccines and carries an EpiPen, but had not used it yet.  Patient's vitals were normal. She was given diphenhydramine for her symptoms, which did not improve.  The Emergency Department was consulted, who advised that patient should be transported to the ED and monitored for 4 hours.  The cardiologist transported patient to ED via wheelchair.  The following day, patient reported she was released from the ED after 4 hours of observation.  All of the symptoms had subsided at the time of release from the ED, and she was back to baseline on 3/4/21.    The patient was referred to an allergist for consultation and clearance prior to receiving a second dose of Pfizer vaccine. Also of note, upon review of the patient's vaccine consent form, she did not acknowledge that she had previous anaphylactic reactions to other vaccines, nor was this information relayed to the vaccinator who administered the vaccine.  Upon return to clinic, the patient reported she was 5-6 weeks pregnant.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Around 8 pm (about 6 hours after receiving the vaccine) I started to feel typical flu symptoms such as chills and aches, and I had some body shaking as well. I was in bed that night and the symptoms kept getting stronger, and around 11 pm I started to feel tingling throughout my body, mostly in my hands and feet. It was very uncomfortable to lay still and I felt I'd never be able to fall asleep if I couldn't lay still. I took 10mg of Z-Quil around 11:30 pm. My body and skin was also starting to get very hot, I never took my  body temperature but I probably had a fever. I put a cold compress on my forehead. I also took 1000 mg acetaminophen and 400 mg Advil. I got up to use the bathroom and I could walk but my balance was off and I felt tingling up my legs. I laid back in bed with the cold compress again and the tingling in my hands and feet increased. I tried walking around again and again felt tingling up my legs. I sat on the edge of my bed moving my feet around which helped the tingling, but when I laid down again the tingling kept coming back. I took another 10mg of Z-Quil and 0.25mg xanax (prescription for anxiety). I finally decided to move to a chair with lots of pillows so I could sit upright since that helped reduce the tingling. I finally fell asleep sometime after 12:30 am. I woke up in the chair around 2 am and was feeling better - no tingling, no body shaking, chills and aches were reduced and body temperature didn't feel as high. I was then able to sleep in bed for the rest of the night. The next day I still had aches and chills and a fever but it was manageable with Advil or acetaminophen, and by Monday (March 8) I was able to go to work.
OTHER_MEDS: 300 mg sertraline, birth control pill, daily multivitamin

CRP 91.4 mg/L,  D-Dimer 2340 ng/mL.  Patient was admitted, diuresed, and started on inpatient COVID protocol which included Ivermectin. PCR positive and negative results were relayed to accepting facility - facility and they were going to refer to epidemiology for follow up.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 20 minutes after injection, I began feeling progressively warmer as if I had beads of sweat on my forehead.  I began to feel light as if my body was light. The Lead Monitor came over and had my blood pressure and oxygen levels checked over the next 40 minutes before I felt actually fine and able to walk out.  At no point did I have trouble breathing although that question was repeatedly put to me.  Then at home I took it easy but noted anything out of the ordinary. 1.5 hrs after the injection and lasting only 2 minutes, I felt like a band was being tightened around my head to the point of discomfort but not pain. 24 hrs after the injection, for less than one minute, my left temple felt pressure as if I had a head cold. I haven't had a headache in a decade so this was unusual for me. 10 hrs after the injection, I was awakened to by cramping from lower Achilles to foot in my right leg only. This lasted painfully for 12 minutes.  My right foot  itself felt numb. I would stand to stretch the muscle/ tendon but then immediately felt nauseous. I hate feeling nauseous so I would lay back down only to have to stand again due to the pain of the persistent  cramping. This was 12 minutes of excruciating leg cramps. When usually I might have only one or two very brief leg cramps per year. 14.5 hours after injection, I awoke very thirsty adn my skin felt very dry. I drank water and applied hand lotion. Thereafter the vaccine site felt sore but the injection site would have been invisible but for the bandaid outline that narrowed down where the injection had to have been located. The vaccine site was never red or pink or raised at all. Just a pin prick if you really looked for it.  As a follow-up, the second Pfizer dose was Lot  EM9809 on Feb. 26, 2021, and I had no reaction at all. No visible injection site in right arm, no warmness, no light-headedness, no cramps, nothing at all happened.
PRIOR_VAX: Cholera vaccine decades earlier; passed out off and on for 2 days

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Summary: Syncopal espisodes x 2   16 yo patient received his Covid-19 vaccine and as he was going to sit down in observation, he leaned on his mom and passed out. His mother gently lowered him to the ground (@ 1804). Patient's mother stated he just passed out and that this was his first injection ever in his life. Patient was immediately assessed by multiple nurses. Patient did not fall or hit his head or injure any part of his body. Patient took less than 60 seconds to respond to verbal commands and comprehend what had happened. Patient's legs were immediately raised and vital signs were obtained. He was diaphoretic and pale but both were dissapating.  Patient denied difficulty breathing, pain, discomfort. Patient was moved to a reclined chair. Patient and family at side (mother and father) agreed to be monitored. At 1828, Patient complained of feeling "a star" on the left side of his chest. Patient was unable to describe this further. I asked if he was feeling anxious and he said yes. I instructed patient to take several deep breaths in through his nose and out through his mouth. After doing this 3 times, patient stated he did not feel anything funny in his chest anymore. At 1835, while still seated in a reclined chair, patient passed out again. He was pale and diaphoretic. A few team members saw him jerk/twitch and it was questionable if he was having a seizure. The jerking did not last but a few seconds. 911 was called @ 1826. Patient was transferred to a wheelchair and put in the ambulance @ 1841. Vitals were obtained throughout and charted. Pulse ox saturation levels were not below 96%. Immediately after the patient passed out the second time, his pulse was measured at 38 bpm and his lips displayed slight cyanosis. His pulse quickly rose to 52 bpm, within less than 10 seconds. One minute later his pulse was up to 68 bpm.

Pt denies COVID sx  2nd ED note:  Pt arrived to ED via EMS from community health center S/P Covid vaccination.  About 15 minutes after receiving vaccine - felt nausea and smelled "medicine" followed with upper lip swelling and numbness to tongue associated with difficulty swallowing and redness to forehead.  Pt alert and oriented at this time.  Speaking in full sentence, drinking bottled water without any difficulty. No drooling noted.  Denies SOB, chills or fever.   Emergency Department Attending Attestation Note   See resident/PA/student note for further details of HPI, history, exam, ED course, and diagnoses.   Briefly, this is a 51 y.o. female with PMH reviewed in chart and w/ patient notable for insulin dependent diabetes, depression, prothrombin mutation, migraine, p/w concern for allergic reaction.  Emesis or change in Covid vaccine today.  10 minutes after receiving the vaccine, patient reports feeling thick in her tongue with tingling in her lips.  Patient was given Zertec.  The minutes later, her lips began to swell up and was also noted to have new erythematous rash between her eyes and forehead.  Patient was given 50 mg of Benadryl.  Patient felt like she could not swallow with worsening lip swelling.  She was given EpiPen and 911 was called. No stridors.  No wheezing.  Reports continued tingling and the numbness in her mouth but no lip swelling or tongue swelling.  Denies any difficulty swallowing at this time.  No wheezing.  No abdominal pain or nausea.  No rash at this time.   Of note, patient also notes left-sided facial, arm, and leg numbness starting about 10 minutes prior to arrival to the emergency department.  She reports that she has had recurrent numbness on the left side in the past, which was thought to be due to migraine versus TIA.  She has had extensive work-up and multiple hospitalization for this symptom.  She reports that she is allergic to iodine and gadolinium containing contrast.  Denies any headache at this time though she had a mild headache after receiving the vaccine.  Denies any blurry vision.  Denies any weakness in her bilateral upper and lower extremities.  Assessment and Plan:    Vital signs notable for O2 sat of 96 to 98% on room air without tachypnea.  Patient is mildly hypertensive.  Patient is well-appearing speaking full sentences without any dysarthria.  Pupils are equal and reactive to light.  Extraocular movement intact.  She notes diminished sensation to her left face, left upper extremity, and left lower extremity.  Tongue is midline.  Hearing is intact bilaterally.  No facial droop.  She has 5 out of 5 strength in bilateral upper and lower extremities.  No pronator drift.  Normal gait.  No tongue swelling or lip swelling.  No stridors.  No uvula swelling.  No pharyngeal or erythema.  Lungs are clear to auscultation bilaterally without wheezing or rhonchi.  Cardiac exam without murmurs rubs or gallops.  Regular rhythm.  No abdominal distention or tenderness on palpation.  No CVA tenderness.   51-year-old female who is presenting to the emergency department with improving lip swelling and numbness in her mouth, raising a concern for anaphylaxis related to her Covid vaccine.  Reassuringly, status post EpiPen, her symptoms are improving.  However, she has new onset left-sided numbness, with without any headache.  She reports that she has had this numbness in the past the last time she had the numbness on the left side was approximately 10 years ago.  Her neurologic exam is only notable for diffuse numbness on her left side including her face.  Differential diagnosis include migraine headache and TIA.  Stroke is possible though less likely given the patient has had the same symptoms in the past with negative work-up.  Will defer code stroke at this time but will emergently consult neurology.  Will get labs including BMP and CBC.  We will continue to monitor her from the anaphylaxis perspective.  We will also give her a dose of steroid.  Prednisone 60 mg by mouth given 12:29 PM  NEUROLOGY CONSULT NOTE  Assessment: Formulation- Diagnosis is guarded. Localization structurally would suggest subcortical (thalamic) or small brain-stem in a sensory territory on the right. Etiologies could be stroke given her vascular risk factors but seems unlikely given there is stereotypy of earlier symptomatology. Demyelinating would be another possibility as well, but again, the stereotype. Seizure unlikely because of the timing of rush from toes to body was minutes and duration of some occasions being days. Complicated migraine possible, has some risk factors, but should be treated as dx of exclusion. She does make complaint of headache, which could support. Some FND elaboration on her anxiety-ridden allergic reaction is also possible, but no objective non-structural signs to support.

LTC Pharmacy was notified of a potential vaccine related hospital admission on 3/8/2021. The following information was gathered from discussion with RPH at Hospital. The patient received second dose of Pfizer COVID vaccine on 2/26/2021. The patient then had nausea, vomiting, and poor oral intake. On 2/27/2021, the patient went to the bathroom and while on the toilet, had a vasovagal event which led to her hitting the side of the face while falling. Patient was then taken to the hospital for evaluation. The patient does have a pacemaker but the cause of the event was determined to likely be due to dehydration. Lab work was performed and pertinent lab values include: potassium of 3.1, SCr of 0.8, and BUN of 13. The patient received potassium supplementation and IV hydration in the hospital. Patient was discharged on 2/28/2021. Of note, the patient does have a pacemaker and a follow-up appointment with cardiology to evaluate the pacemaker was scheduled upon discharge.

Then the other leg, or sometime multiple locations at once. I didn't feel cold at the time. This lasted for 40 minutes total. I took 1000 mg Acetaminophen at  3:00 am.  Then, as the shaking lessened, I became very cold. I put on lots of clothes and laid on a heating pad under my comforter. Sometime later, I became very hot. Patient received the 1st dose of the Pfizer vaccine on Feb. 17, 2021.  On or about Feb. 22 or Feb. 23, 2021, she began to notice trembling in her jaw.  She told me (her mom) about the trembling on Feb. 25.  She had just increased her dosage of Venlaxafine on Feb. 21, 2021, so we actually thought that the jaw tremor was due to that.  As a result, at the direction of her psychiatrist, we began to taper off the Venlaxafine beginning on March 1.  Over time, the jaw tremor was less noticeable.  However, on March 10, 2021, patient received the 2nd does of the Pfizer vaccine.  The next day, March 11, 2021, the jaw tremor was worse than ever.  I can see the tremor - basically, her lower (?) jaw trembles and you can see the trembling in her mouth and chin.  It does not cause pain, and she does not have any other symptoms (no chills, fever, body aches, rashes, difficult breathing, etc.).  We talked to her pediatrician and to her psychiatrist.  Neither one could say what is causing the tremor; perhaps it is the COVID vaccine; perhaps it is the Venlaxafine (she's not all the way off of it yet); perhaps something else.  However, given the timing of the tremor, and given that the strength of the tremor seemed to get better but then got worse again the day after the 2nd COVID vaccine shot, I wanted to report it.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within five minutes of getting the vaccine I felt the front of my neck/throat had something like pressure/pressing/swelling.  I kept swallowing and it didn't feel like my throat, more like between the outside of my throat/esophagus and skin...in the position where a man's Adam's apple would be, or possibly where my thyroid is.  I got flushed, but I could breath ok.  I felt odd, but I think I may have been panicking, I don't know.  I drove home and saw that my face, neck, chest, even my thighs, were slightly flushed.  I took my temperature throughout the evening.  I am normally a low temperature of 97.6.  It went up to 99.9.  The second day my temperature was in the low 98s.  However, by second day the roof of my mouth where it meets the throat felt odd, like if you burned it by eating something hot.  Third day, today, I woke up and my temperature was only 95.2.  I kept taking it, and then used my daughter's thermometer as well.  It stayed low for several hours.  I also had several bouts of diarreah this morning.  Temperature came up into the 98s again.  None of this is life threatening, but I still feel the weirdness in the front of my neck.  I've never heard of that side effect so it upset me and scared me.  I can handle the fever also, but the low temperature also scared me.
OTHER_MEDS: Collagen, Goli Apple Cider VInegar Gummies, Seed Probiotics, GEM Cacao nutrient dense Bites, Earth Echo Cacao Bliss Superfood Elixer Blend, Matcha Tea

Received 2nd dose of Pfizer COVID vaccine on 2/24/21. No reported adverse reaction at that time. On 3/10/21, developed worsening of chronic back pain. On day of event, took a dose of celecoxib and rivaroxaban (concurrently). He had been avoiding taken chronic celecoxib since at least the time of his last COVID-19 vaccination, and potentially took this fairly rarely due to concern for interaction with his DOAC.   Beginning about 5 minutes after these medicaions were taken, patient felt weak/strange and asked his wife to take him to ED. In ED he was initially somnolent but arousable, but then developed hypotension and hypoxemia. Given IV benadryl initially, but then acutely worsened with development of facial, hand, and neck swelling. Reportedly had substantial "frothing at the mouth." Treated with SQ epinephrine, IV methylprednisolone, IV famotidine and was intubated with difficulty. Started on an epinephrine infusion due to persistent hypotension (dose up to 0.1 mcg/kg/min) and transferred to referral center ICU (reporting center). On arrival here, notable hand edema, some facial edema.  Ventilator support rapidly weaned to minimal settings. Evaluation and hospitalization ongoing.  Overall clinical assessment is anaphylactic reaction to celecoxib unrelated to COVID-19 vaccination.

I was able to eat, brush, and floss normally. If it had not gotten better, I was going to go to the dentist because it seemed something was really wrong. I have been on immune suppressants for over 10 years. I had not heard that sensitive gums was a side effect. So, I thought I should let you know. The other side effects I had were crohn's symptoms due to my immune system becoming more active. My eyes because sensitive and extremely dry. I was woken up one night because my eyes were burning. I had to put eye drops in my eyes to be able to go back to sleep.  I am still having milder side effects one week after the shot. Saturday, Marth 5th -- day after vaccination.  Upon awakening, extreme pain head-to-toe, in muscles and joints.  Severe headache (very rare for me), Hands could barely move (like severe arthritis),  Slightly elevated temperature (98.9 when my normal is 97.8).  Overall symptoms faded slightly and then returned to full strength two or three times during the day.  Unable to eat (not nauseous, just not hungry) and only drank water.  No bowel movement and very little urination during the day.  By about 18:00, headache was gone and pain was receding .  Around 21:00 started getting very cold and could not seem to get warm.  Started shaking severely from cold.  Put on sweat suit, turned on bed heater, and added blankets, then went to bed around 22:00.    Woke up Sunday morning (March 7th feeling absolutely perfect!  None of the previous day's pain was present, no temperature, no limits to hand/finger movement, and was very hungry.  Ate a normal size breakfast with no problems, urination was normal,   It was like the reaction had never happened, but my wife assured me that it had.   Other than slight constipation, I have no had any problems since.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had a severe sarcoidosis attack Sept-October. I am taking methotrexate 5 mg for that. I had the first  vaccine 12/30/20. 3 weeks later had a bump on the left leg. second dose 1/29/21. within a week there  was a sarcoid rash on the right leg (3x4 inches). My chronic cough increased mid January, and became  uncontrollable through March first. There was the stomatitis as well. I also had arthritis flareup in the  hip and finger. All began to improve March 2, 2021.

30 minutes after the shot I got a scratchy throat for about an hour. 4 cough drops and 1 hr latern it  went away. Tuesday evening I felt like I had a bit Of the flu-just like after a flu shot. But Sunday morning  around 8 am in the shower I noticed red bumps on my ankles. These continued to spread up my legs  during the day. A lot of them! I took Zyrtec and in the evening there were more including on the back  upper side of my arms. A lot of them! By Monday morning after a miserable night my lower legs below  the knees to ankles were covered and more on my body. I went to the doctor. Believe this is a reaction  to the Covid 19 shot. Taking two 24-hour a day Zyrtec and using Calamine lotion. Still ongoing 3/11.

Within hours I quickly became extremely sore, fatigued, and had difficulty breathing. I was unable to eat  until the breathing issues subsided late afternoon Sunday since I felt as though I was choking when I  attempted to eat. The fatigue and body pain was pronounced enough for me to have to call off work  Monday, but they gradually diminished. I am submitting this on 3/11, and I am still experiencing some  body aches though the constant feeling of exhaustion is no longer present.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I am starting this report with the current status of my, nearly, 6-week ordeal of  agonizing pain, doctor appts. debilitation, pain meds, a blood test and the final  MRI � this past Saturday, 3/6.  Finally, an MRI has confirmed physician's recent suspicion that my  second Moderna vaccination was improperly administered. In fact, it tore a  tendon in my right shoulder. I knew something was wrong when I saw how high  the needle was injected into my arm/shoulder. I just didn't know what the  ramifications would be.  I have been referred to a surgeon, and my appt. is 3/16).  Summary of Events:  On 2/1/21, I received my second dose of the Moderna vaccine and had 2 days  of moderate pain and soreness.  But about 3 days later, 2/4, I awoke to excruciating shoulder/arm pain that had  me sobbing out loud. I took Tylenol and waited. Nothing. I took more Tylenol and  slowly the pain diminished. For an hour or so.  All I could do was lie on the couch, literally, groaning and unable to lift my arm  By evening, the only relief I could get was from an old (hip surgery) Oxycodone pill. I took 1/4 piece and slept the night.  Friday and Saturday I was totally debilitated. I couldn't lift my arm, care for my  dog or do anything but lie on the couch, still sobbing, until small pieces of the  Oxy set in again.  It was the weekend, and I didn't want to bother anyone but I never felt such pain  for such an extended time or survived so long on meds.  Monday morning, 2/8/21, I called my Doctor. I was very  concerned and really wanted to make sure this pain was still from the vaccine  and not some "weird" condition that might have hit me. The office told me the  pain was probably from the vaccine and advised me to keep taking Tylenol. So it  continued, on and off, relief and agony. I was sure it would stop. It didn't.  Thursday, 2/11, I saw the Doctor, in person.  Physician did not have an answer for the pain but gave me a prescription for  Celebrex and did a blood test to see if there was a bacteria infection that might  have invaded the area. We would wait for results. Another weekend of pain but  lessened a bit.  Around 2/13, a neighbor called me with an article he found about the SAME  situation MANY people were suffering (thousands) and LAWSUITS pending!! I  didn't know what was happening to me but the Gov't did. The article was found  on internet, 2/12, and printed an article from news paper, 2/12  No  other reports appeared anywhere. The pertinent findings of the article: thousands of vaccinated people (Covid and  flu) have reported similar pain and debilitation. The previous gov't has  introduced a law prohibiting lawsuits (l think against the pharmas but not the  administering agencies. Not sure.) that was to go into effect, 2/23. Again, not sure  of details.  But no one knows about this - people NEED to know. I immediately notified my  family and close friend about my situation. While the cause is not certain, it is  suspected that improper injection technique/training/experience is to blame.  To get the word out, I posted on social media, wrote representatives, etc.   And now I found you. The information must be made available; not to stop  vaccinations but to alert the public if they occur.
LAB_DATA: Blood test 2/12/21        MRI  3/6/21 - Torn Tendon + Negative for bacteria                      other - right shoulder
OTHER_MEDS: Rivastigmine 9.5 patch Losartan 25 mg., Escitalopram 10 mg

SYMPTOM_TEXT: congestive heart failure; inadvertently administered another dose (3rd dose); tested positive for Covid-19; A spontaneous report was received from a nurse and other health care professional for a 91-year-old male patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced congestive heart failure, tested positive for Covid-19 and inadvertently administered another dose (3rd dose).  The patient's medical history was not provided. No concomitant product use was reported.  On 22-JAN-2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: not provided) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 23-JAN-2021, 1day after receiving the vaccine the patient was hospitalized due to congestive heart failure. The patient had difficulty of breathing at that time.   On 03-FEB-2021, the patient tested positive for covid-19. The patient was transferred to a rehabilitation facility on an unspecified date to recuperate.   On 25-FEB-2021 at around 11:30 in the morning, the patient was given second dose of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: not provided) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of covid-19 infection at a rehabilitation facility. On the same day at around 02:30 PM, a group of vaccine providers came and inadvertently administered another dose (third dose) of the vaccine mRNA-1273 (lot number: not provided) to the patient. Apparently, there was two patients with the same names, and they did not check the birthdays. The health care professional reported that at the time of this report, the patient was in the hospital and was on a ventilator. Treatment information included ventilation.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 was not applicable.  The outcome of the events, congestive heart failure and tested positive for Covid-19 was unknown and the outcome for the event inadvertently administered another dose (3rd dose) was recovered/resolved.  The reporter did not provide the assessment for the event's congestive heart failure, tested positive for Covid-19 and inadvertently administered another dose (3rd dose).; Reporter's Comments: COVID-19 in this patient is unlikely to be related to Moderna COVID-19 vaccine. Based on the current available information and temporal association, a causal relation between the product and congestive heart failure cannot be excluded. Medication error of extra dose administered for (mRNA-1273), lot # unknown  was reported, with no associated AEs reported after the additional dose.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: bladder felt full, like they could not empty it; limited bowel function; vomiting that day; limited appetite; dry mouth; felt very dizzy; extreme tiredness for 3 weeks; A spontaneous report was received from a healthcare professional concerning a 65-year-old, female patient, who experienced urinary retention, dizziness, vomiting, fatigue, decreased appetite, dry mouth  and limited bowel function.  The patient's medical history, as provided by the reporter, included two time cancer survivor . Concomitant medications reported included Carvedilol for high blood pressure, acetamide for cholesterol, potassium, multivitamins, zinc, calcium, Vitamin D.  On 05 Feb,  prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 031L20A) in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   Patient was ok at midnight, but when they woke up, they felt very dizzy, were vomiting that day, and experienced extreme tiredness for 3 weeks, now they feel relatively recovered, like 90%, but still somewhat tired, probably related to not been able to eat on account of having very limited appetite. They mentioned they had limited bowel function, and their bladder felt full, like they could not empty it. Patient states they had a dry mouth from  the beginning of the symptoms.  After a week of these symptoms, on Saturday, the patient went to a clinic and they did some bloodwork and found that the liver enzymes were elevated and 5 more values were not normal and that their kidney function was not normal.  They consulted with their oncologist and they believed these could be an extreme immune response to the vaccine, since the lab work conducted on the 23Dec2020 was normal.  Last Friday they have some blood tests and the values were back to normal.  Treatment for the events included paracetamol and ibuprofen alternating; and  Prednisone.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported.   The events, dizziness, vomiting, fatigue, dry mouth were relatively recovered, like 90%, but still somewhat tired.  The outcome events,  urinary retention,  decreased appetite,   and limited bowel function are unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Thursday, March 11th, 2021 approximately 3:10 pm, Patient received his first dose of Moderna Vaccine (Lot number: 003A21A) in his left deltoid  Patient received the Moderna Vaccine. After which he sat in the designated medical observation area for 15 minutes. Approximately five minutes later around 3:15 pm, Patient experienced syncope, fell out of his chair, hit the left side of his forehead on the ground. Due to the fall, he experienced a mild abrasion on the left side of his forehead, which led to bleeding.  The Physician?s Assistant rushed to aid Patient who was lying on the ground in a supine position. Emergency Medical Services (EMS) - Fire Department and ambulance were called immediately and approximately five minutes later EMS arrived. During the time frame prior to EMS arrival, the Physician?s Assistant asked numerous questions to Patient to assess his condition. She asked Patient if he could breathe and he responded ?yes?. She asked Patient  if he was short of breath and he responded ?no?. She asked Patient if he felt like his throat was closing and he responded ?no?. At this point, an Epinephrine pen was not used.  Patient was alert and the Orient x 4 questions were asked [(1) Who are you? (2) Where are you? (3) What is the date and time? (4) What just happened to you?]. Patient also denied head pain, neck pain, nausea or chest pain. Staff performed a limited neuro-exam and was deemed within normal limits. Patients Glasgow Coma Scale score was 15 Patient  mentioned that he has a phobia of needles and something like this has happened before when he was ?young?. Patient initially did not want an ambulance to be called. It was explained to him that it might be in his best interest to call EMS due to syncope and abrasion on his forehead due to the fall. Patient also mentioned that he only consumed two cookies and coffee for that day.  When the EMS arrived (about 5 firefighters), they interviewed him and performed a blood pressure test. His sitting blood pressure was 130/82. One of the firefighters assessed his spine and Patient denied cervical, thoracic, and lumbar tenderness or pain. The firefighter assessed Patient's glucose level, which was a bit difficult to obtain in the first initial efforts, with the glucometer reading ?error?. The firefighters eventually were able to obtain a reading on Patient's glucose and it read 86. Patient was able to stand on his own, and a second blood pressure test was performed; his standing blood pressure reading was 145/89.  EMS gave Patient gauze to address his head wound Patient initially refused to go to the hospital, but per EMS protocol, fluids needed to be administered. Patient entered the ambulance and was taken to the hospital by EMS.
LAB_DATA: -Orient x 4 questions were asked [(1) Who are you? (2) Where are you? (3) What are the date and time? (4) What just happened to you?]. -Blood pressure test. His sitting blood pressure was 130/82. The standing blood pressure reading was 145/89. -Spine assessment -Glucose reading. His blood glucose was 86

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Exactly 2 week after receiving the second Covid-19 vaccine shot I woke up in the morning with a serious balance issue.  I felt like I was on a rocking boat.  This was a constant feeling, with some days worse than others, but balance was off for two weeks.  I also experienced slight "fogginess", which is still an issue.  I have never experienced any type of balance in my entire life.  This was most concerning.  After doing some intensive research, I found an article that some that recieved the vaccine did have some vestibular issues, balance/dizziness.  Which makes me think that my episode was vaccine related. I am only reporting this so that you can track a possible non-typical adverse reaction.  I am in no way indicating the vaccine was defective.
LAB_DATA: I made an appointment for a Videonystagmograph, however, by the time I had the test complete, my balance issues seemed to have cleared up. Preliminary results from the test indicated that I did not have a vestibular weakness present at time of the test.  My ENThad prescribed prednisone and meclizine to help alleviate the symptoms.  It did take a good 2 weeks for my balance to come back to normal.
OTHER_MEDS: Nortriptyline, Fish Oil, Probiotic, CoQ10, Lysine, Bioidentical Hormone Treatment, Vitamin D

She literally thought she was going to die given the severity of her weakness.  As quickly as the symptoms occurred, they left her on March 7th, 2021.  She went to work on March 8th and noted similar symptoms to prior ITP flares - petechiae on legs, gum bleeding, fatigue, mild headache.  She also noted dark urine but no frank blood.  Since being admitted and receiving steroids, she is feeling improved and petechiae are lessening.  She also noted mild mouth ulceration to lower lip along with oozing.

patient received his first dose of the Moderna Covid-19 vaccine. After receiving in our immunization room, he left the room and then shortly walked over to the pharmacy in-window and told the pharmacy tech that he did not feel well and felt dizzy. Tech had him go sit down in the waiting room and went and got the nurse, who went out to check on patient. Patient was slumped in the waiting room chair with eyes closed and very sweaty. Patient said he wanted water, so staff quickly got him water. After a few sips, patient's head rolled back and he lost consciousness for roughly 10 seconds before waking up startled and confused. Ambulance was already called and when the arrived they triaged the patient for around 15 minutes. After about 15 minutes the patient seemed much better and the paramedics decided it was OK for him to leave and drive himself home.

sore arm; dizziness; This case was reported by a consumer via call center representative and described the occurrence of pain in arm in a 77-year-old female patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   On 30th September 2020, the patient received the 1st dose of Shingrix (intramuscular). On an unknown date, less than 3 months after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced pain in arm and dizziness. On an unknown date, the outcome of the pain in arm and dizziness were recovered/resolved.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the pain in arm and dizziness to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: The patient received her 1st dose and had a sore arm and dizziness for approximately 2 days. For tolerance in 2nd dose refer case refer case US2021008399. This case is also been linked with US2021021112 and US2021008399, reported by the same reporter. fever; chills; pain (from head to toe) / soreness; This case was reported by a consumer via call center representative and described the occurrence of fever in a 83-year-old female patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   The patient's past medical history included chickenpox (had chickenpox as a child) and shingles (had as an adult and hospitalized because of it). Previously administered products included Covid-19 vaccine with an associated reaction of no adverse event (received on an unknown date) and flu vaccine with an associated reaction of no adverse event (received on an unknown date).   On 18th December 2020, the patient received the 1st dose of Shingrix (intramuscular). On an unknown date, less than 3 months after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced fever, chills and pain. On an unknown date, the outcome of the fever and chills were recovered/resolved and the outcome of the pain was not recovered/not resolved.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the fever, chills and pain to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: The patient had reported the case for herself. The patient received 1st dose at her local pharmacy. The patient experienced a fever, chills, pain from head to toe and soreness. The patient thought it was Covid-19. The adverse reactions lasted for about two and a half days, however, the soreness was still there (not severe but was bothersome). The reporter provided limited information and did not have the lot number and expiration date. The reporter did not give permission to follow-up with her health care professional.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Chickenpox (had chickenpox as a child); Shingles (had as an adult and hospitalized because of it)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Second dose / on 3/3/2021 and received the first dose 7/2020; Chills; Bodyaches; Headache; Nausea; This case was reported by a consumer via call center representative and described the occurrence of chills in a 53-year-old male patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   Previously administered products included Shingrix (1st dose was received on an unknown date in July 2020).   On 3rd March 2021, the patient received the 2nd dose of Shingrix. On 3rd March 2021, unknown after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced drug dose administration interval too long. In March 2021, the patient experienced chills, general body pain, headache and nausea. In March 2021, the outcome of the chills, general body pain, headache and nausea were recovered/resolved. On an unknown date, the outcome of the drug dose administration interval too long was unknown.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the chills, general body pain, headache and nausea to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: The case was reported by the patient for himself. The patient received the 2nd Shingrix dose, late than the recommended schedule, which led to lengthening of the vaccination schedule.  After vaccination, the patient developed chills, body aches, headache and nausea. The patient stated that he felt better and all symptoms were resolved at the time of reporting. The reporter consented to follow up.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Day of vaccine (Tues 3/9): Mild headache, injection site soreness.  I can't tell if it's related, but I couldn't really focus on work-related tasks - I don't know if it was just the nervousness of waiting for side effects or what.  Day after vaccine (Wed 3/10): Mild headache that came and went through the day (I took acetaminophen in the early evening), tiredness, injection site soreness (noticed bruise forming), and felt "off" - not quite nauseated, but not normal self.  Same lack of focus/productivity.  Two days after vaccine (Thur 3/11): No headache, injection site soreness waning (but bruise is bigger), not as tired, better focus, but in the evening, I felt a hard rounded node above my collarbone (about two fingers wide).  Freaked out, Googled it, saw swollen lymph nodes on side of vaccine site is somewhat typical.  Appears to be my left supraclavicular lymph node and if you look hard enough, you can visibly see the left side is slightly swollen.  I cannot feel any other swollen lymph nodes.  Today (Fri 3/12):  Bruised injection site, and this swollen, hard lymph node is quite sore.  Other than that, I feel fine at the moment.
LAB_DATA: None - Since I see swollen lymph nodes are somewhat typical, I really don't want to spend $30 co-pay to have my doctor tell me it's a normal reaction and to keep an eye on it...I will contact my doctor if/when it gets any more painful or doesn't go down in a week or so.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: nerve pain; lasting side effect of muscle or nerve pain; ongoing pain in his thigh; This case was reported by a consumer via interactive digital media and described the occurrence of nerve pain in a male patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   In January 2021, the patient received Shingrix. On an unknown date, less than 3 months after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced nerve pain, muscle pain and pain in thigh. On an unknown date, the outcome of the nerve pain and muscle pain were unknown and the outcome of the pain in thigh was not recovered/not resolved.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the nerve pain, muscle pain and pain in thigh to be related to Shingrix.  Additional information was provided as follows: The age at vaccination was not reported. The events were reported by the patient's wife. The reporter stated that, the patient received vaccine in early January this year and had ongoing pain in his thigh since then. The patient also probably had muscle and nerve pain. The reporter inquired if it was possible for the Shingrix vaccine to have a lasting side effects of muscle or nerve pain.

I slept a bit and around 3 p.m. was finally able to drink a little water. Still very weak but pain had subsided significantly, down to about a 4 / 10.  By 6 pm. I was almost pain free ? symptom free though very weak still. On day of Wednesday day of Moderna vaccine shot, felt good all day, got ready for bed at 9 PM.  Felt very warm and took my temperature it was 99.7.  Not too bad.  My hands and feet were very cold.  Put socks on my feet and climbed in bed.  Feeling ok.  Woke up around 4 AM my tee shirt is soaking wet, had to pee.  Got out of bed and walked to bathroom no problem.  Sat down and then my wife said she heard a loud noise in bathroom.  She comes to check on me and I?m sitting on toilet passed out, I?m leaning to my right against the shower door.  She?s hollering and talks to me to wake up and shakes me and eventually I wake up, get up and walk to the bed no problem.  Then I feel the urge to vomit.  Go through a series of dry heaves, lay on my back and feel urge to vomit again.  Wife tells me to lay on my side, not on my back, that works and I fall asleep.  Woke up Thursday at 8 AM, wife is in the kitchen, I make the bed get dressed and feel ok.  Walk out to the kitchen and wife is amazed I?m OK.  She proceeds to tell me about my passing out in the bath room.  I have no recollection that occurred.  Had some tea and toast, drinking water to rehydrate and felt better.  Walked outside, got leaves out of the pool.  Feeling better.  No further reaction, just a little tired the rest of the day.  Had light lunch, soup.  Took a nap at 3 PM woke refreshed and had normal dinner with a glass of wine.   Today Friday had normal breakfast and feel completely normal.  All in all not a bad reaction.

COVID19 Pfizer-BioNTech dose 1 administered as above (on 1/6/2021) COVID19 Pfizer-BioNTech dose 2 Lot #EL8982 on 1/26/2021  A 15 year old child of an employee received dose 1 and dose 2 as described with no medical adverse events, however outside of FDA EUA and State COVID-19 vaccine eligibility criteria.  administered vaccine to her child the first week of expanded access to vaccine beyond healthcare workers and other Tier 1a individuals.  On investigation, did not document these doses within the health or patient medical record systems, however did document the administration within the state vaccine tracking system.  On further investigation, stated that she administered the first dose of vaccine at the end of the day, when extra doses had been prepared and the employee stated that they did not want to waste a dose of vaccine.  During the hospital's investigation, a number of contributing factors were also identified, including three different electronic record systems and the need for manual entry of all vaccine administration into, in addition to one of the two other systems, as well as balancing prepared vaccine supply with demand.  These systematic gaps have been closed and through process change as well as electronic safeguards, future events will be prevented.

Immediately after receiving the vaccine, I felt pretty good. Just some soreness in arm and a minor headache an hour later. I took Tylenol and symptoms were bearable the rest of the day. By around 6 or 7p that night, I experienced full body pain and chills, similar to the flu. I also had some chest pain and tightness but attributed that to the overall body pain. I was also very winded and short of breath. I called my Primary Care Doctor to report this, and she said this was a normal reaction and it meant my immune system was working. It continued into the next day, and I took my temperature and had a 102 fever. I slept most of the day and was unable to work. I also had a severe headache. The next day, on Day 3, my flu symptoms were getting better; however, I felt dizzy and short of breath. I also fainted . This is the first time this has ever happened to me. I have never fainted in my life. My symptoms seemed to resolve after eating and drinking, so I figured it may have been dehydration. On Day 4, I was concerned because I was having shortness of breath and chest pain, along with dizziness. I could not take a deep breath without having pain. I called my Primary Care Doctor, and she told me she was concerned I might have covid and to go to the ER. I do not believe I have covid. No one in my household has these symptoms except for me. I believe it is from this vaccine. My chest pain/shortness of breath seemed to go away. for a bit so I did not go to ER. I'm on Day 5 now, and the chest pain/shortness of breath has come back, so I decided  to report this because I do not listed on the list of common side effects for the Johnson and Johnson vaccine. I joined a J&J social media group where others are also reporting these symptoms, so I decided to report to Vaers. I also have had night sweats every day since taking the vaccine and my blood pressure is lower since taking the vaccine.
OTHER_MEDS: Armour Thyroid, Low Dose Naltrexone, Nortriptyline

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Rash below 2nd Shingrix vaccine; This case was reported by a consumer via interactive digital media and described the occurrence of rash in a adult patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   On an unknown date, the patient received the 2nd dose of Shingrix. On 3rd March 2021, unknown after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced rash. On an unknown date, the outcome of the rash was unknown.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the rash to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were reported as follows: Age at vaccination not applicable. The age group was not reported but it was selected as adult as per the vaccine indication. On the day before reporting date, the patient experienced rash post 2nd dose of shingrix.

Bright red spot on big left toe / continues to be bright red; It itched a lot / itching; Big toe got crusty; Big toe / had blisters; This case was reported by a consumer via call center representative and described the occurrence of erythema of extremities in a 77-year-old female patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   The patient's past medical history included shingles (mild case of shingles years ago after hysterectomy) and hysterectomy (years ago). Concurrent medical conditions included drug allergy (allergic to tetracycline, levaquin, macrobid, lasix).   On 26th December 2020, the patient received the 1st dose of Shingrix (intramuscular). On 10th January 2021, 15 days after receiving Shingrix and an unknown time after starting mupirocin and Valacyclovir, the patient experienced erythema of extremities, pruritus, crust and blister. The patient was treated with mupirocin, valaciclovir hydrochloride (Valacyclovir) and azithromycin (Z Pak). On an unknown date, the outcome of the erythema of extremities was not recovered/not resolved and the outcome of the pruritus, crust and blister were recovered/resolved.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the erythema of extremities, pruritus, crust and blister to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: The case was reported by the patient for herself. The patient received the Shingrix vaccine into the left arm.  The lot number and expiry date were not provided by the reporter. 2 weeks later, the patient developed a bright red spot on big left toe, it itched a lot but was not painful. Her podiatrist gave ointment TAC mupirocin 2% which was helping. Her dermatologist gave zpak and valacyclovir which helped for itching.  The patient's big toe got crusty and had blisters and she also used vinegar and water and crusty blisters resolved. Her left big toe continued o be bright red.  The patient had her first COVID (Corona Virus Disease) vaccine on 3rd March 2021. The reporter did not consent to follow-up.; Sender's Comments:  US-GLAXOSMITHKLINE-US2021057758:Same reporter.
CUR_ILL: Drug allergy (allergic to tetracycline, levaquin, macrobid, lasix)
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: Hysterectomy (years ago); Shingles (mild case of shingles years ago after hysterectomy)

Within 5 minutes, I felt burning sensation in my chest; in 10 minutes - I started getting chills and within 15 minutes chills were a lot worse. After about 25-30 minutes after I felt like my blood pressure dropped and I actually passed out and once I passed out I don't know how long I was out for. Maybe less than a minute, I couldn't breathe and I was hyperventilating and they put a oxygen mask on me. They took me to ER (Hospital) and I recognized I was in there when I "woke up" - they were trying to get an IV in me but I was shaking so much it took several attempts. They gave me several medications because I was nauseated as I wanted to vomit and they gave me anaphylactic medications. I was having chest pains. I fell asleep. They were going to admit me but I kind of refused to be admitted and they let me go with Zofran, prednisone and one other medication. One of coworker took me home. I slept the rest of the day and night. The next day, Really fatigued and chest pain was semi getting better. Breathing - was pretty okay after that. By day 3, I was fine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I woke Sunday morning (03/07/2020) feeling itchy around the injection site on my upper left arm. I showered and applied coconut oil to the area and the itchiness subsided. The itchy feeling returned at the end of the day, but was tolerable. I awoke the next morning and the site was itchy, hard, slightly swollen and  hot to the touch. It was visibly red and bumpy. That morning I felt very cold, tired and had a bad case of diarrhea. I took a nap, and when I woke I felt much better.  That afternoon and evening I applied cold compresses to the site which helped to soothe the discomfort. It took several days for the swelling and rash to go away. After receiving the first dose of the Moderna vaccine, I had a very minor, dull headache - pressure behind my eyes and left side of my head.  My body felt fatigued and sore like I had a very intense workout where my muscles were burning from exertion.  These all subsided after about a day and a half.  Exactly 8 days later, my left arm (same injection arm but NOT at the injection site) felt itchy.  When I looked at my arm, there was a huge, oval shaped, red, swollen, hard bump on the front of my shoulder.  The skin also felt very leathery.  I wasn't sure what was going on and it was Friday and my doctor's office had already closed.  I spoke with a pharmacist where our family gets prescriptions and he asked if I had any other types of symptoms.  I did not.  He said had not heard of this type of reaction from the vaccine this many days later and directed me to call my primary care if it didn't clear up in a couple of days.  It did clear up.  First the leathery skin went away the next day, followed by the redness and swelling and then after a couple of days it still felt slightly itchy but visually, the location looked like my normal skin.  I did not contact my doctor because coincidentally, that weekend, I saw an article pop up on my phone about Covid arm and the description was identical to what I experienced.  I will mention it to my doctor when I go in for my second dose but figured I would report it on .
